abstract: Costa Rican Foreign Ministry announces first humanitarian transfer of stranded Cuban migrants will send them from Costa Rica to El Salvador, part of deal reached by Central American officials to allow stranded migrants to continue journey to United States.
lead_paragraph: The Costa Rican Foreign Ministry said in a statement that the first humanitarian transfer will airlift Cubans from Costa Rica to El Salvador in January.

headline.main: Costa Rica: Some Stranded Cubans to be Allowed to Continue North
headline.print_headline: The Americas; Costa Rica: Some Stranded Cubans to Be Allowed to Continue North
